The paper proposes a new method for semi-supervised learning on graph structured data, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on graph convolutional networks and proposes a new method called Lovasz Convolutional Networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper deals with graph structures and classification tasks.
